11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 26 O.S. 2021, Section 14-108.1, is
13 amended to read as follows:
14 Section 14-108.1. A. Neither a notary public nor an agent
15 working on behalf of a notary public shall be authorized to:
16 1. Request absentee ballots on behalf of a voter other than
17 himself or herself;
18 2. Assist a voter in requesting absentee ballots, other than
19 for himself or herself or a member of his or her household;
20 3. Receive by mail an absentee ballot on behalf of a voter,
21 other than for himself or herself or a member of his or her
22 household; or
23 4. Submit a completed absentee ballot on behalf of a voter
24 other than for himself or herself.
