1 B. 1. A notary public shall maintain a log of all absentee
2 ballot affidavits that he or she notarizes for a period of at least
3 two (2) years after the date of the election. The log shall include
4 the name of the voter and the date, time, and method of
5 identification.
6 2. a. A notary public who is authorized to notarize more
7 than twenty absentee ballot affidavits at a single
8 election, as provided in paragraph 3 of subsection C
9 of this section, shall submit a copy of the log to the
10 secretary of the county election board who granted the
11 written permission. The copy of the log must be
12 received by the secretary of the county election board
13 no later than the close of business on the fifth
14 business day following the date of the election.
15 b. The log shall be a public record and shall be
16 maintained by the secretary of the county election
17 board pursuant to Section 3-126 of this title.
18 c. A notary public who fails to submit the log as
19 required by this section, or who notarizes more than
20 twenty absentee ballots without authorization pursuant
21 to paragraph 3 of subsection C of this section, shall
22 have his or her notary public appointment revoked for
23 eight (8) years by the Secretary of State.
24
